            <p>With the exciting launch of our new ATMs, I wanted to get some feedback to gain an understanding of where
              we had succeeded and where there was room to continue to iterate. With returning users and new users with
              bitcoin wallets it was a blow out success. The main area of friction and potential improvement is for new
              users who do not have a bitcoin wallet upon interacting with the ATM. 1/3 of tested users found the task
              of creating a wallet on the spot a deterrent from beginning or continuing the checkout process. A solution
              for this problem could potentially be a paper wallet but leaves users open to lost funds due to accidents
              or lack of education. More research and testing needs to be done in order to find the best way to improve
              those drop off findings.&nbsp;</p>
